     1	"""Accept/reject corpus, shared by the per-model and parity tests.
     2	
     3	Each case is a ``(name, data, should_pass)`` tuple. The corpus is the
     4	single source of truth; its pairs drive both the Pydantic model tests
     5	and the JSON Schema parity test. An asymmetry between the two would
     6	mean a drift in the parity surface and is what the schema-parity job
     7	catches.
     8	"""
